Feature: macOS headless launch avoids Keychain prompts
  AgentChrome-managed Chrome launches must stay non-interactive for AI agents and CI.

  @regression
  Scenario: macOS managed profiles avoid Keychain prompts
    Given AgentChrome launches Chrome with an internally managed temporary user data directory on macOS
    When the Chrome argument list is built
    Then the launch arguments include keychain-avoidance flags

  @regression
  Scenario: Headless launch succeeds without workaround flags
    Given no AgentChrome session exists
    When the user runs "agentchrome connect --launch --headless"
    Then AgentChrome returns "ws_url", "port", and "pid" with exit code 0

  @regression
  Scenario: Explicit Chrome args are preserved
    Given the user supplies additional "--chrome-arg" values
